phrases.phrase: 어렵긴 하겠지만, 당신은 해낼 수 있어요.
meanings: 개인 신상 It's hard, but you can do it.

examples.korean: I’ll try to fix it — but it’s not trivial. 발음듣기 내가 그걸 고쳐 보기는 하겠지만 그게 간단하지가 않아. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: I’ll try to fix it — but it’s not trivial. 발음

examples.korean: We’ll have to be careful with money but that doesn’t mean (that) we can’t enjoy ourselves. 발음듣기 우리가 돈에 신중해야 하겠지만 그렇다고 우리가 즐기지도 못한다는 뜻은 아니다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: We’ll have to be careful with money but that doesn’t mean (that) we can’t enjoy ourselves. 발음

examples.korean: I’ll see what I can do but I can’t promise anything. 발음듣기 내가 뭘 할 수 있을지 보기는 하겠지만 아무것도 약속할 수는 없어요. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: I’ll see what I can do but I can’t promise anything. 발음

examples.korean: He won’t say a dicky bird, but we think he knows who did it. 발음듣기 그는 한마디도 안 하겠지만 누가 그걸 했는지 그는 알고 있다고 우리는 생각한다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: He won’t say a dicky bird, but we think he knows who did it. 발음

examples.korean: I’ll work till late in the evening, but my weekends are sacrosanct. 발음듣기 제가 저녁에는 늦게까지 일을 하겠지만 저의 주말은 신성불가침입니다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: I’ll work till late in the evening, but my weekends are sacrosanct. 발음
